title: Area Boys Cross Country: Knoxville third at Prairieland Meet
text: Posted Oct. 1, 2015 at 10:34 PM Updated at 10:34 PM Posted Oct. 1, 2015 at 10:34 PM KNOXVILLE — The Knoxville High School boys cross country team placed third out of fifth teams at the Prairieland Conference Meet on Tuesday. Elmwood/Brimfield dominated the meet with six top 10 finshes and a score of 20. Rushville-Industry was second with 60, the Blue Bullets finished with 71, Farmington took fourth with 90 and South Fulton had 125. Peter Alfano led Knoxville with a seventh-place time of 17:37.2. Hunter Carlson crossed the line in 12th in 18:14.06, Matt Thompson was 14th in 18:18.54. Donovan Burton finished in 19:04.7 for 22nd and Cooper Wilt was 38th in 21:22.89. Abingdon-Avon was represented by three runners led by Andrew Powell’s sixth-place time of 17:37.2. Ben Stipp took 15th in 18:20.32 and Doug Havens was 42 in 23:30.77. Logan Johnson ran the course in 19:24.96 cod 26th-place for Bushnell-Prairie City. Ethan Singleton was 28th in 19:40.59 and Remington Lindsey took 47th in 26:13.32 for the Spartans. The Register-Mail
